<h3 id="head-htmltag">`<html>`-tag</h3>

It has proven helpful to use [Paul Irish's](http://paulirish.com/2008/conditional-stylesheets-vs-css-hacks-answer-neither/) and later used and enhanced by [HTML5 Boilerplate](https://github.com/h5bp/html5-boilerplate/issues/425/#) conditional tag bomb around the head-tag, i.e.:

<pre data-rel="html" class="prettyprint lang-html">
	<code>
		<!-- paulirish.com/2008/conditional-stylesheets-vs-css-hacks-answer-neither/ -->
		<!--[if lt IE 7]> <html class="no-js lt-ie9 lt-ie8 lt-ie7" lang="en"> <![endif]-->
		<!--[if IE 7]>    <html class="no-js lt-ie9 lt-ie8" lang="en"> <![endif]-->
		<!--[if IE 8]>    <html class="no-js lt-ie9" lang="en"> <![endif]-->
		<!--[if gt IE 8]><!--> <html class="no-js" lang="en"> <!--<![endif]-->
	</code>
</pre>

(Note that you shouldn't have to tailor your code to IE9...)

